<p><span style="color:red">Butterfly pea flower tea</span> is made from the ternatea flowers and dried lemongrass and changes color depending on what is added to the liquid, with lemon juice turning it purple.[19] In Thailand and Vietnam, this butterfly blue pea flower tea is commonly mixed with honey and lemon to increase acidity and turn the beverage a pink-purple color, to produce for a drink usually served after dinner, or as a refreshment at hotels and spas.[20] The drink is a typical local drink like chamomile tea is in other parts of the world The tea is found in both hot and cold varieties.</p>
